cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with deep learning models for natural language inference, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses adversarial methods and neural models, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of artificial datasets and models for natural language inference also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on fairness in evaluations could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) as well.
